    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>If Teachers Are Heroes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert W Carr letter on Sept 28 article calls for higher pay for teachers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Novice's Hard Lesson: Bringing Order to a Class'' (front page, Sept. 28):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''A Novice's Hard Lesson: Bringing Order to a Class'' (front page, Sept. 28):</p>
        <p>If every era needs a hero, ours should be Donna Moffett, who you report gave up a good job as a legal secretary to teach at a troubled school in Brooklyn. The good news is that there are people like her. The bad news is that we will need many, many more Ms. Moffetts in the next 10 years. We'd better start paying teachers for the heroes they are -- or we'll never get them. And then who will teach the children to read?</p>
        <p>ROBERT W. CARR  Ann Arbor, Mich., Sept. 28, 2000</p>
      </block>
